content: One day of use. The user interface looks old, but I like that. No unnecessary fluff draining my battery! The warm up video crashed when I briefly used another app, so don't switch apps mid-workout! Besides these minor issues, the app's perfect!

I don't have a kitchen table that supports my 80Kg, and I cannot destroy my door knobs by hanging from them. You don't need equipment, but just super strong medieval furniture that would hold a horse! I've uninstalled the app and asked for a refund. Too bad since I liked what was offering.

I have had this app on my phone for a couple of years. Always with intentions to do the guided programs. I started several times but because of excuses I stopped. About a year ago I started working out in earnest and I started with some generic app to help me. Over the next 6 months or so I used several different apps that I enjoyed and was able to lose 30 pounds. I hit a rough spot and didnt work out for a few months and to get myself back into it I decided to start the you are your own gym program. Now I'm in week 9 of the program and it's been pretty different from the other apps I've used. For one I haven't lost a single pound, but I believe I'm losing inches and I can tell that I'm stronger. I feel better and have more energy which was my original goal anyways. What I like about the guided program is that I feel like it stretches you but it also feels possible to do. I also like the variety of it because I find I get bored when I do the same workout week after week. Hands down though I would recommend this to anyone. I think no matter your fitness level you can jump in and get something from Mark Lauren's program.

For the basic workouts that come with this app, it's pretty good. It handles a variety ways to structure the workout and you can select a variety of exercises, substituting for cases where you can't do a particular exercise that day due to fatigue or injury. Where it falls apart is attempting any sort of custom workout. There's no option to hold an exercise for more than 9 seconds despite several stating that you should be holding it for longer periods of time. The repetition parameter is ignored. Workouts that require you to repeat the same set of exercises as a circuit repeatedly only run one circuit and then tell you your workout is complete. I have seen reviews stating that this was a relatively recent thing, broken by an update.  Outside of that, the app is prone to freezing, particularly between exercises, and will sometimes start up an exercise 15-20 seconds in, acting as you started before they told you to start.  The developers need to spend a bit of time fixing their product to actually work again. Of course, given their links still point to forums defunct for over a year, I'm not optimistic about them getting to this.

content: It provides exercise programs that are well-balanced and simple enough that pretty much anyone can do them (if an exercise is too hard, you can change variation to something easier). The only thing missing is that while the app does record reps and you can view them individually in the log, there are no graphs or tables to show how you're progressing. Add that (or Fitocracy support), and this would be a 5 star.  (Oh and for those considering this app, even though it's technically not required, get a pull-up bar. It works a lot better than using a table or door edge for the let-me-ups)
Perfect compliment to his book. His workouts will push you. Don't quit. DO PT!

Nice concept but the first workout I launched (Intermediate) allotted 7 minutes for 1 repetition. Not sure if that is intentional or a bug?  EDIT: Finally figured out how this works. These are ladder workouts, start with 1 rep, then hit Increase Reps button. Keep doing this, increasing the reps. After each set of reps, the app gives you a rest period equal to the time it took you to do the reps.
Super useful app, thanks. Please make an easier way to compare repetition count between sessions.
Great excercises, program, instructions, everything... I love the quick workouts

Also I accidentaly skipped workout saving afterwards, and I don't have the opportunity to save it once skipped. I'd like to have an option, that every workout gets saved by default. If you've read "You are your own gym" by Mark Lauren, then get this application. It's the perfect complement to the book. The latest version is basically a redesign of the app based on customer feedback, and features a redesigned and improved interface, completely updated (re-shot and clearer) photos, improved text descriptions, and the ability to save, edit and create workouts. On top of that, there's even 500mb of videos you can download, for free. Full marks to Leafcutter Studios for creating a great app, and for listening and responding to customer feedback.

Installed this on my nexus 7 and was very impressed with the detail and functionality. I am just super impressed with this whole package.  The book (which you should purchase if you're going to pursue this program, although read on...) is inexpensive and the app is a drop in the bucket.  And you get a lot more than what you pay for.  I'm three weeks into the program, so it's not like I know exactly what trajectory I'm on, though, feeling healthily sore all the time is an awesome signal.  But I can say with confidence that this is an extremely well crafted workout application.  Throw your phone in an armband, plug in some headphones so you can hear the trainer instructions, and jump into your workout clothes, and you're good to go.  I was already impressed with this app the past three weeks.  But the new redesigned UI just blows me away.  Integrated videos. Vastly better workout descriptions.  Streamlined, elegant, and frankly pretty UI...  Just stunningly excellent.  Could not recommend this app more highly.
